The paper combines data from a massively multiplayer online first person shooter game with ground-truth data on player demographics, play style, psychometrics, and friendships to investigate the impact of friendship on performance in competitive environments. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including social and information networks (cs.SI), computational complexity (cs.CY), game theory and economics (cs.GT), sound and music computing (cs.SD), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). However, given the focus on social networks and their impact on competition, cs.SI is the most likely sub-category.
